===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[deviation]] from a rule or from what is regarded as normal; an [[outlier]].
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1956|author={{w|Arthur C. Clarke}}|title=The City and the Stars|page=43|passage=This ardent exploration, absorbing all his energy and interest, made him forget for the moment the mystery of his heritage and the '''anomaly''' that cut him off from all his fellows.}}
#: {{syn|en|abnormality|deviance|deviation|exception|inconsistency|irregularity|phenomenon}}
# Something or someone that is [[strange]] or [[unusual]].
#: {{ux|en|He is an '''anomaly''' among his friends in that he's the only one who's unmarried.}}
# {{lb|en|science}} Any [[event]] or [[measurement]] that is out of the [[ordinary]] regardless of whether it is [[exceptional]] or not.
#: {{ux|en|She disregarded some of the '''anomalies''' in the experiment, putting them down to miscalculation.}}
# {{lb|en|astronomy}} Any of various [[angular distance]]s.
# {{lb|en|biology}} A [[defect]] or [[malformation]].
# {{lb|en|quantum physics}} A failure of a classical [[symmetry]] due to quantum corrections.
# {{lb|en|dated}} An [[irregularity]] or [[disproportion]].

